{
  "matrix_version": "1.0",
  "description": "The explicit five-target by channel support matrix for the composite A2A product (dashboard executable + adjacent immutable A2A capsule as one release set) — a2a-product-provisioning plan W01.P01.S146. Every supported channel installs the SAME logical release set (ADR constraint). `support_status` is `supported` (product-owned, proven), `feasibility_gated` (a package-manager channel whose support is contingent on the phase-zero clean-machine install/upgrade/downgrade/repair/uninstall proof in `.github/workflows/a2a-channel-feasibility.yml`, gated by W01.P01.S148 — a channel without a proven reversible adapter is NOT a supported update channel, ADR D2), or `unsupported` (with a reason). Self-installed copies let the external updater helper own file activation and rollback; package-manager-owned copies use a two-phase adapter (manager stages/activates/rolls back; the product helper does preflight/drain/snapshot/verify).",
  "channels": [
    "self-install",
    "msi",
    "scoop",
    "winget",
    "cargo-binstall",
    "cargo-install"
  ],
  "targets": {
